					<h4>Western Book Roundup</h4>
		
		<h1>Western Lit Conferences, Trade Shows, and Bookstores, Oh My</h1>
		<h2><i></i></h2>
		<div class="text-feature_print">
							<p>By Jenny Shank, 8-12-09</p>
			
			
							<p>The <a target="_blank" href="http://www.awpwriter.org/conference/2010headlinersbios.php#jharjo" title="Association of Writers &amp; Writing Programs">Association of Writers &amp; Writing Programs</a> will hold its annual conference in Denver next year, April 7 thorough 10.&nbsp; Michael Chabon will give the keynote address, and some well-known Western writers (as well as some not-so-Western ones) will be there.&nbsp; Rick Bass, Joy Harjo, Robert Hass, George Saunders, Danzy Senna, Leslie Marmon Silko, Gary Snyder, Terry Tempest Williams, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/an_interview_with_david_wroblewski/C39/L39/" title="David Wroblewski">David Wroblewski</a>, and many others will be on hand to read from their work and discuss literature.&nbsp; 
</p>
<p>
Farther down the food chain, I&#8217;ll be moderating a panel called &#8220;To West or Not To West,&#8221; organized by Colorado fiction writer <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/an_interview_with_steven_wingate/C39/L39/" title="Steven Wingate">Steven Wingate</a>, author of one of my <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/best_western_books_of_2008/C39/L39/" title="favorite books from last year">favorite books from last year</a>, <I>Wifeshopping</I>.&nbsp; The authors on the panel will be Wingate, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/laura_pritchetts_call_to_dive_in_dumpsters_and_ditch_western_womens_stereot/C39/L39/" title="Laura Pritchett">Laura Pritchett</a>, Marilyn Krysl, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/an_interview_with_robert_garner_mcbrearty/C39/L39/" title="Robert Garner McBrearty">Robert Garner McBrearty</a> and <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/an_interview_with_janis_hallowell/C39/L39/" title="Janis Hallowell">Janis Hallowell</a>.&nbsp; Wingate described the topic in this way:
</p>
<p>
&#8220;Fiction writers in the West inevitably find themselves face to face with two forces: the region&#8217;s role in America&#8217;s cultural mythos and the shadow of &#8216;the Western&#8217; as a genre in fiction and film. Many writers with roots in the West do not write &#8216;western&#8217; fiction, yet feel their aesthetics and subject matter being influenced by the life of the region. This panel will explore the variety that Colorado fiction writers respond to the West at a time when the identity of the region is shifting.&#8221;
</p>
<p>
I&#8217;ve never moderated anything before, so I&#8217;m hoping that these writers are tame.&nbsp; I&#8217;ll pack bear spray just in case.&nbsp; Also, the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.mountainsplains.org/tradeshow.aspx" title="Mountains and Plains Independent Booksellers Association">Mountains and Plains Independent Booksellers Association</a> is holding its tradeshow in Denver next month (September 23-26, Crowne Plaza Hotel DIA).&nbsp; There will be author appearances by Rick Collignon and Jaqueline Kelly, whose books were the MPIBA&#8217;s first &#8221;<a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/reading_the_west_gets_the_word_out_about_regional_books/C39/L39/" title="Reading the West">Reading the West</a>&#8221; selections, and on September 25 the regional book award winners will be announced.&nbsp; I&#8217;ll be there to blog or Twitter or whatever the preferred form of communication six weeks from now will be.&nbsp; If you see someone wandering around with a dazed expression because she hasn&#8217;t been out of the house without her kids in a year, say hello.&nbsp; Quietly.&nbsp; Because I&#8217;ll be jittery.
</p>
<p>
In a recent editorial, Clay Evans of the Boulder Daily Camera <a target="_blank" href="http://www.dailycamera.com/news/2009/aug/04/banking-on-bricks-mortar/" title="praised Barnes &amp; Noble">praised Barnes &amp; Noble</a> for &#8220;ignoring all the gloomy predictions and opening a new &#8216;hard copy&#8217; store on Aug. 12.&#8221; 
</p>
<p>
Please follow me on <a target="_blank" href="http://twitter.com/jennyshank" title="Twitter">Twitter</a>, and <script type="text/javascript">
